title: MonsterCross Mayhem - The Levee Breaks
description:
A one of a kind cycling adventure from Fort Worth to Dallas and back. Singletrack, road, paved trails, horse trails, levees/jeep roads, and maybe even a water crossing or two.

Staging will be at Trinity Bicycles in downtown Fort Worth and the group will depart en masse to the Trinity Trails system to follow the levee trails to the Gateway Park Mountain bike trail.

From there riders will follow a marked course combining paved trails, roads and jeep roads to the River Legacy Mountain Bike trail in Arlington.

The next segment will be mostly paved road and paved trails from Arlington trhough Grand Prairie and into the Dallas County Levee trails and ultimately to the LB Houston Mountain Bike Trail.

The final leg will be a short pedal over to the DART train station and take the train back to downtown Fort Worth and then pedal back to Trinity Bicycles in fantabulous Sundance Square.
course: Approximately 75 miles of combined singletrack, paved trail, levee roads and paved roads. Course will be marked and cue sheets will be provided.
registration: https://www.bikereg.com/Net/17606
directions:
Trinity Bicycles
343 Throckmorton St.
Fort Worth, TX 76102

title: Pace Bend Road Race
description: Located on scenic Lake Travis in the rolling hills west of Austin in Spicewood, Texas, the Annual Pace Bend Road Race is one of the largest cycling races of the Spring season.
course: As one of the few events in Texas to feature full use of the roadway (no \"center line\" rule), cyclists from all over the southwest have found the race\'s classic 6.2 mile circuit, punctuated by sweeping curves and short, steep climbs, a prime opportunity to test themselves.  It\'s an excellent course for spectators to get up close to the action.
registration: NO RACE DAY REGISTRATION. Register online at www.bikereg.com/17902 - until Friday, February 22, at 11:45PM.  Online registration fees apply. In-person registration will be allowed at packet pickup at Mellow Johnny\'s 400 Nueces, on Saturday, February 23rd for an additional $20 fee.  Pre-Registered riders may pickup their race packet on race day beginning at 6:45 AM, but are strongly encouraged to pick-up at Mellow Johnny\'s on Saturday.  A race parking discount will be offered to those who pick-up on Saturday.All USA Cycling riders MUST present their current USA Cycling license to the Registrar in order pickup their bib number.
notes:
Parking: On-site parking will be clearly marked and volunteers will be there to assist.  IMPORTANT: Entrance to the park is $10 per vehicle; and it\'s CASH ONLY.
*CFC* - Combined Field Limit
directions: From Austin, TX, take US 71 West approximately 30 miles to RR 2322 (Pace Bend Park Road.)  Turn right on RR 2322 and travel 4.6 miles to the Park entrance.

title: USAC Regional Talent ID Road Camp (St. Edward

Midnight Massacre
description:
The Midnight Massacre is a metric century(ish) gravel grinder starting at 8 pm near Sanger, TX. The route will primarily be made up of dirt/gravel roads as well as some short and desolate paved segments. Headlights and tail lights are required but this should be an excellent way to beat the summer heat in Texas and take in a new type of adventure. 

We will also be offering a shorter 30-40 mile route as an alternate. This would make a great intro to gravel grinding or allows the early risers to get to bed at a decent hour.

Organizers will NOT be providing any sag vehicles or support during the route. You are welcome to have your own support vehicles out on the course if you are not comfortable participating in a self supported metric century at night.
course: Mix of gravel, pavement and rough pavement.

course:
A unique adventure ride featuring the Northeast Texas Trail.
A combination of rails to trails trailway (improved and unimproved), dirt roads and limited paved roads. Various ride lengths for all levels.
notes:
This is an adventure ride, not a competition. There are no prizes or awards. There will be towns along the way with access to water and food but there will not be SAG vehicles or aid stations. Please consider this a a self supported ride. Do not enter if you are not comfortable riding without support.
Ride the NETT is a unique adventure ride utilizing the Northeast Texas Trail as well as a network of dirt and country roads for the longer routes. The NETT is a converted railway line which is still very rugged along much of it's path. Mileage and routes may change at promoters discretion based on weather, trail and road conditions or as warranted for safety purposes.
Either mountain bikes or CX bikes would be appropriate but we do not recommend road bikes at all. We offer numerous route lengths for most skill levels. Registration is online only @ https://www.bikereg.com/net/ride-the-nett which closes 8pm 11/1.
Out of town visitors are welcome to bed down in the Methodist Church gymnasium Friday evening with Saturday breakfast for a small donation. Please let us know if you plan to utilize this option. 
Kiddie Train - Farmersville to Celeste and Back (all NETT)
directions:
Downtown Farmersville, TX at the corner of Main and Farmersville Parkway.

For questions please email spinistry@gmail.com
